I've had it for months, and it still looks and functions like new, which is a testament to its excellent durability.Organizational Efficiency (5/5): This folder has been a game-changer when it comes to keeping my documents organized. It features multiple pockets and dividers that help me categorize and separate different types of paperwork. It's perfect for keeping track of important documents, whether it's for work, personal projects, or school.Ease of Use (5/5): The folder's user-friendly design makes it a breeze to use. It opens and closes smoothly, and the pockets are generously sized to accommodate various document sizes without cramming or damaging them. The clear label slots on the cover and spine make identifying contents quick and easy.Versatility (5/5): This folder's versatility is a standout feature. I've used it for business meetings, organizing tax documents, and even for keeping my favorite recipes neatly stored. Its adaptability to a wide range of needs makes it an invaluable tool.Value for Money (5/5): The folder offers excellent value for the cost. Given its quality, durability, and organizational features, it's a wise investment for anyone seeking to streamline their document management.In conclusion, this folder has proven to be an outstanding addition to my office supplies. Its top-notch quality, organizational efficiency, and versatility have made it an essential tool for staying on top of my paperwork and projects. If you're in search of a dependable and durable folder to simplify your document management, I wholeheartedly recommend this one. It's a five-star product that has brought order and efficiency to my daily routine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 5, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Great for storage, not for everyday use
reviews.reviewText: It's a fine filer but the labels fall out of their holders and the paper pockets are somewhat flimsy. The tab holder is open on both the top and bottom. The paper pockets are a little too thin to keep papers in place. For a folder where you'll store documents you don't need to look at often (for me, it's bank statements and credit card agreements) it's great. If you're thinking of using it for filing school or work documents that you will be leafing through often, it's not quite sturdy enough to keep your papers in place.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for organizing printed documents, such as notes, flight details and recipes.
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the SMEAD Poly ten-pocket folder. So far I have used it to organize HR documentation, such as medical plans and 401K details. This Poly pocket folder is helpful for someone who is starting a new job who needs to organize a number of on-boarding documents. Students could also use this folder to store lecture notes for various classes. Individuals could also store printed copies of recipes in the folder. Also, individuals could store all their travel information (such as tickets, itineraries, receipts, hotel details and maps) in the folder since it can hold more documentation than a traditional two-pocket folder. Since the folder has ten pockets, it's able to hold up to 25 sheets. It also includes tabs so you can easily subdivide documents. I like that the folder is durable and sturdy. It won't tear. In my book, this is a great product!
Not the highest quality plastic but these folders are meant to be that way. Definitely more study than I expected though and great for organizing sheets for my office.

Good product. Liked the rich blue colour. Good stiffness for covers. Needed to use tape to keep the labels in the slot. 10 pockets is including the front and back cover. (Staples used to have the same named product but had 10 pockets in the pages plus also the front and back)
